1 Overview
**********

The ‘casmgr-server’ Debian package is a thin installer.  It installs:

   • A single systemd unit (‘casmgr.service’) that runs the all-in-one
     container.
   • The compose file ‘/etc/casmgr/docker-compose.yml’.
   • Admin scripts under ‘/usr/lib/casmgr/bin/’ (symlinked in
     ‘/usr/sbin/’).

   PostgreSQL/pgvector, the Code Analysis MCP daemon, and all workers
run inside one all-in-one Docker container (‘vasilyvz/casmgr’),
supervised by s6-overlay.  Inside the container the daemon runs as
‘root’ (‘CASMGR_ALLOW_ROOT=1’) and PostgreSQL drops to UID/GID 999.
There is no application code or Python venv on the host.

   *Version lock:* the Debian package version equals the Docker Hub tag
for ‘vasilyvz/casmgr’.  The full image reference is stored in
‘/usr/share/casmgr/docker-image’ at install time.

Host filesystem layout
======================

‘/etc/casmgr/config.json’
     Server configuration (mode 640, group ‘casgrp’, *conffile*).
‘/var/casmgr/secrets/.env’
     PostgreSQL passwords (mode 640, ‘casuser:casgrp’, *conffile*).
‘/etc/casmgr/mtls/’
     Server and client mTLS material (mode 0750, ‘root:casgrp’).
‘/var/casmgr/postgres/data’
     Database cluster files (bind-mounted, UID 999).
‘/var/casmgr/postgres/cache’
     Database cache directory (bind-mounted, UID 999).
‘/var/log/casmgr’
     Application logs; ‘/var/log/casmgr/postgres’ for PostgreSQL inside
     Docker.
‘/var/casmgr/data’, ‘faiss’, ‘locks’, ‘backups’, ‘trash’, ‘versions’
     Application storage paths referenced from config.
‘/etc/casmgr/docker-compose.yml’
     All-in-one compose stack run by ‘casmgr.service’.
‘/usr/lib/casmgr/bin/’
     Admin scripts (‘casmgr-pg-set-password’, ‘casmgr’).
‘/usr/share/doc/casmgr-server/config.json.template’
     Reference copy of the shipped config template.
‘/usr/share/doc/casmgr-server/CASMGR_DEPLOYMENT.md’
     Narrative deployment guide.

   Only ‘root’ or ‘casuser’ may run PostgreSQL admin scripts.


