3 Installation
**************

     sudo dpkg -i casmgr-server_1.6.35-1_all.deb
     sudo apt-get install -f

   ‘postinst’ on ‘configure’:

  1. Creates ‘casuser’ / ‘casgrp’.
  2. Installs ‘/etc/casmgr/config.json’ from template if missing;
     generates ‘instance_uuid’.
  3. Generates ‘/var/casmgr/secrets/.env’ with random passwords if
     missing.
  4. Installs ‘/etc/casmgr/docker-compose.yml’ if missing.
  5. ‘docker pull’ for the pinned image.
  6. Enables ‘casmgr.service’.
  7. Starts ‘casmgr’ only after config placeholders and mTLS are ready.
  8. Prints a post-install checklist on the terminal.

   On first start the container runs ‘initdb’, creates the ‘vector’
extension, and provisions the application role and database
(‘code_analysis’) from secrets, so no separate database-bootstrap step
is required.

Post-install checklist
======================

  1. Edit ‘/etc/casmgr/config.json’: replace ‘CHANGE_ME’,
     ‘MCP_PROXY_HOST’, set ‘watch_dirs’.
  2. Review ‘/var/casmgr/secrets/.env’ (passwords auto-generated on
     first install); back up securely.
  3. Install mTLS files under ‘/etc/casmgr/mtls/’.
  4. ‘sudo casmgr-pg-set-password’ after editing passwords.
  5. ‘sudo systemctl start casmgr’ when config and certificates are
     ready.


