6 Secrets
*********

File: ‘/var/casmgr/secrets/.env’.  Loaded by systemd
(‘EnvironmentFile’), admin scripts, and the daemon via ‘password_env’.

‘POSTGRES_SUPERUSER_PASSWORD’
     Target password for PostgreSQL superuser (‘postgres’).  Also used
     as ‘POSTGRES_PASSWORD’ when the Docker container is first created.
‘CODE_ANALYSIS_POSTGRES_PASSWORD’
     Application role password; referenced by
     ‘code_analysis.database.driver.config.password_env’.
‘POSTGRES_SUPERUSER_CONNECT_PASSWORD’
     Optional.  Current superuser password when
     ‘POSTGRES_SUPERUSER_PASSWORD’ is being rotated and differs from the
     cluster password.
‘POSTGRES_DB’
     Database name created in the container (default ‘code_analysis’).

   On first install, random passwords replace ‘CHANGE_ME_*’
placeholders.  Back up this file securely.

   After any edit, apply to the running cluster:

     sudo casmgr-pg-set-password

   Superuser only:

     sudo casmgr-pg-set-password --superuser-only


