9 PostgreSQL container
**********************

PostgreSQL runs *inside* the all-in-one container (uid/gid 999, started
via ‘gosu’ by s6-overlay), listening on ‘127.0.0.1:5432’ within the
container.  It is not published to the host and needs no separate
container or systemd unit.

   Data and logs live under the ‘/var/casmgr’ and ‘/var/log/casmgr’ bind
mounts:

Host ‘/var/casmgr/postgres/data’
     Cluster data directory (uid 999)
Host ‘/var/casmgr/postgres/cache’
     Cluster cache directory (uid 999)
Host ‘/var/log/casmgr/postgres’
     PostgreSQL logs

   On first boot s6-overlay runs ‘initdb’ and ‘CREATE EXTENSION vector’,
then provisions the application role and database from
‘/var/casmgr/secrets/.env’.  Inspect it with:

     docker exec casmgr gosu postgres psql -U postgres -d code_analysis -c '\dx'


