10 Ports and co-existence with dev
**********************************

On one host, production and a git-checkout dev server must not share the
same MCP port or proxy ‘server_id’:

Production (‘/etc/casmgr/config.json’)
     MCP port *15010*, ‘registration.server_id’ ‘code-analysis-server’
Development (repo ‘config.json’)
     MCP port *15000*, ‘registration.server_id’
     ‘code-analysis-server-dev’
PostgreSQL (Docker)
     ‘127.0.0.1:5432’ — may be shared; use distinct ‘instance_uuid’ per
     server

   Upgrades preserve an existing ‘/etc/casmgr/config.json’; change
‘server.port’ to *15010* if it still uses *15000* and you run both
servers on the same machine.


