12 Command reference
********************

The MCP ‘info’ command exposes a runtime-generated ‘Command reference’
node.  That node is built from the live command registry after all
command hooks have registered their classes and after metadata
finalization has run.

   It includes, for every registered command:

   • command name, category/group, version, and description;
   • input schema properties, required parameters, defaults, enums, and
     ‘additionalProperties’;
   • extended command metadata: detailed description, return contract,
     usage examples, error cases, and best practices when published by
     the command;
   • Git, GitHub, file, project, queue, session, search, worker,
     database, AST/CST, analysis, backup, logging, transfer, and system
     commands registered in the running server.

   Use it through MCP:

     call_server(server_id="code-analysis-server", copy_number=1,
                 command="info",
                 params=node:Command reference,format:text,max_chars:250000)

   Because it is generated from the live registry, the command reference
stays in sync with newly added commands without requiring this static
Texinfo file to duplicate every command description.  The static manual
remains the deployment and operations guide; the dynamic node is the
authoritative full command catalog.


