16 Troubleshooting
******************

Address already in use (MCP port)
=================================

Production uses port *15010*; dev checkout uses *15000*.  Stop one
instance or align ‘server.port’ in config.  Check listeners: ‘ss -tlnp |
grep -E '15000|15010'’.

initdb: Operation not permitted
===============================

Ensure ‘/var/casmgr/postgres/data’ is owned by UID 999 (postgres in the
official image):

     sudo chown -R 999:999 /var/casmgr/postgres/data /var/casmgr/postgres/cache

Server cannot connect to PostgreSQL
===================================

Check the ‘casmgr’ container is running (‘docker ps’), that in-container
PostgreSQL is listening on ‘127.0.0.1:5432’, and that
‘/var/casmgr/secrets/.env’ matches ‘password_env’ in config.  Re-apply
passwords:

     sudo casmgr-pg-set-password
     sudo systemctl restart casmgr

Password rotation failed
========================

Set ‘POSTGRES_SUPERUSER_CONNECT_PASSWORD’ to the *current* cluster
superuser password, update ‘POSTGRES_SUPERUSER_PASSWORD’ to the new
value, then run ‘sudo casmgr-pg-set-password’.

Wrong Docker image version
==========================

Inspect ‘/usr/share/casmgr/docker-image’ and reinstall the matching
package version.

Daemon crash-loops after install
================================

The application venv lives inside the image, not on the host.  Inspect
container logs first; a broken venv means the image must be rebuilt or
re-pulled.

     docker logs --tail 200 casmgr
     sudo systemctl restart casmgr


